issue.body:
I seem to be hitting the same issue as #25983. This was fixed by a modification to OutputStreamSourceStage made by @raboof on Dec 18 2018 (https://github.com/akka/akka/commit/8e0d3e4c96ef64c77f8258284040fbe5e6b19f09) and was marked fixed for 2.5.21. 

However, I can see that issue 26136 was fixed by a commit (https://github.com/akka/akka/commit/b0b0865e4ccefa4bd90224b5f4576357a73b27cc#diff-3fc5b08f30cf4755b842061163961132) on Feb 7 which completely changes the class' implementation (and could conceivably have reintroduced the bug).

We are seeing (extremely occasional) truncation of output stream responses (i.e. issue #25983) with akka-http 10.1.8 / akka-stream 2.5.23. This is a real issue as the (now useless) response is being (legitimately) cached by an intermediate proxy layer, so this is not observed as a transient issue by our users. Here's the code where I write to an `OutputStream`:

      def pipe(f: OutputStream => Unit): Source[ByteString, Any] = {
        implicit val ec = blockingIoPool
        import gsa.shared.scala._

        StreamConverters.asOutputStream(15.seconds).mapMaterializedValue { os =>
          val metered = new CountingOutputStream(new BufferedOutputStream(os, 2 << 13))
          Future {
            val (_, d) = timed(scala.concurrent.blocking(f(metered)))
            finest(f"Piped response to query $q to $os in ${d.fractionalMillis}%,1fms")
            IOResult(metered.getCount, Success(Done))
          }.andThen {
            case _ =>
              try metered.flush() finally metered.close()
          }
        }
      }

I have checked and all `f`s we send to this function `flush` their input anyway. Our logs do not indicate any issues with writing the response stream

Do you have any suggestions as to how I may furnish you with any useful information to help you narrow it down?
